Explanation:
- I searched the repository for usages/definitions of UsersRegister and found its implementation in users/routers.go. That file defines the UsersRegister function:
  - UsersRegister(router *gin.RouterGroup) { router.POST("/", UsersRegistration); router.POST("/login", UsersLogin) }
- The same file also implements the actual handler functions referenced by UsersRegister (UsersRegistration and UsersLogin), plus related user/profile handlers (UserRetrieve, UserUpdate, ProfileRetrieve, ProfileFollow, ProfileUnfollow).
- I ignored test files (there is a call to UsersRegister in users/unit_test.go), per your instruction to focus on the implementation.
